# Node & Template Conventions

## Single Source of Truth for Categories

`nodeDefinitions.ts` exports `inferCategory(type)` — the canonical category resolver.
All other files (aiService, AICopilotPanel, Home) must import from there.
Never duplicate category logic; add new types to `NODE_DEFINITIONS` first.

## Filter Operator Contract

Filter nodes accept these operators in `config.condition`:
- Equality: `==`, `eq`
- Inequality: `!=`, `neq`
- Greater than: `>`, `gt`
- Greater or equal: `>=`, `gte`
- Less than: `<`, `lt`
- Less or equal: `<=`, `lte`

When adding new operators, update both `WorkflowBuilder.tsx` (`executeDirect` filter block)
and `server/src/core/engine/runner.ts` (server-side filter).

## sharedContext Contract

Execution passes data between nodes via `sharedContext: Record<string, any>`.
Node types that write to sharedContext:
- `send_payment`: `.status`, `.amount`, `.txId`
- `tinyman_swap`: `.swap_status`, `.swap_txId`
- `get_quote` / `price_feed`: `.price`
- `filter`: reads from sharedContext, does not write

## Template Config Rules

- Never use placeholder addresses like `ALGO_ADDRESS_PLACEHOLDER` or `TEAM_LEAD_ADDRESS`
- Use empty strings for addresses users must fill in
- Filter conditions must use operators from the supported set above
- Config keys must match what execution logic reads (`amount`, `receiver`, not `amount_from`)

## Adding a New Node Type (Checklist)

1. `nodeDefinitions.ts` — add to `NODE_DEFINITIONS` array
2. `WorkflowBuilder.tsx` — add case in `simulateWorkflow` and `executeDirect`
3. `prompts.ts` — add to the node type list in `AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT`
4. `runner.ts` — add server-side execution case (if applicable)
5. Verify `inferCategory` returns correct category (auto-derived from NODE_DEFINITIONS)

## isReal Semantics

- `true` = real Algorand on-chain transaction (payment, ASA transfer, app call, Tinyman swap)
- `false` = off-chain, simulation-only, or external API (browser notification, spreadsheet, HTTP)
